function extract_julia_code(md)
    code_blocks = split(md, r"^\n{3,}.*\n\n", StringSplitOptions.TrimEntries);

    filtered_code_blocks = map(block -> replace(block, "^```.*```\n?", ""), block), code_blocks);

    joined_code = join(filtered_code_blocks, "\n")

    return joined_code
end
```
This function `extract_julia_code` takes a markdown string `md` as input and follows the specified requirements to extract and format the Julia code blocks.
